      "text": "GR8 Job: BIC journalism students bring home several awards - WMC Action News 5 - Memphis, Tennessee Member Center: GR8 Job: BIC journalism students bring home several awards 2016-04-20T02:30:04Z (Source: Rhonda Metheny) MONETTE, AR (KAIT) - \nThe Buffalo Island Central newspaper and yearbook staffs brought home several awards from the Arkansas Scholastic Press Association this week in Hot Springs. \nThe group of eight students won the following awards: \nSuperior and best of ASPA newspaper multimedia package \nSuperior and best of ASPA online newspaper blog \nBest of ASPA online newspaper sports package \nSuperior and best of ASPA newspaper news story \nSuperior newspaper feature story \nSuperior newspaper sports news story \nSuperior newspaper sports feature \nSuperior and best of ASPA newspaper news photo \nSuperior and best of ASPA newspaper feature photo \nSuperior and best of ASPA newspaper photo essay \nThe BIC newspaper, the Hoof Prints, also won the All-Arkansas award. It is the first time BIC has won that award. \nCamden Metheny was named newspaper editor of the year and Shyla Clayton won photojournalist of the year. \nTracey Thompson has been the newspaper’s advisor for several years and this is her last at Buffalo Island Central. \nIn honor of her last successful competition, the group arrived home in a limousine escorted by local police. They were welcomed back to the school by supporters. \nGR8 Job to Buffalo Island Central’s newspaper and yearbook staffs. \nCopyright 2016 KAIT . All rights reserved. \nWatch Region 8 News On Demand: On your Desktop | On your Mobile device \nRegion 8 News App - Install or update on your: iPhone | Android News on WMCTV.com News More>>",
