      "title": "Why you should quit your job, and the college that's helping students pay off debt",
      "text": "By Priya Anand, MarketWatch\nHello, MarketWatchers.\nSome of history's most famous scientists probably earned a lot less than you\nA look at what notable scientists earned (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/some-of-historys-most-famous-scientists-probably-earned-a-lot-less-than-you-2016-04-20) at different stages of their careers.\nHere's one good argument for not washing your clothes\nThe household item you may not realize you should recycle (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/heres-one-good-argument-for-not-washing-your-clothes-2016-04-20)\nThe best reason we've heard to quit your job\nFull-time workers who change jobs get bigger raises (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/the-best-reason-weve-heard-to-quit-your-job-2016-04-20) than those who stay put.\nSheila Bair's novel idea: Have colleges help pay student debt\nWashington College raised $313,000 (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/sheila-bairs-novel-idea-have-colleges-help-pay-student-debt-2016-04-20) to go toward paying some student loans.\nHow 4/20, the stoner's holiday, went mainstream\nAs legalization progresses, a counterculture movement has become commercialized (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/how-420-the-stoners-holiday-went-mainstream-2016-04-20).\nELSEWHERE ON MARKETWATCH:\nU.S. stocks close at 2016 highs as oil rally continues\nThe S&P 500 closed up 1.60 points (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/us-stock-futures-pull-back-putting-2-day-advance-in-jeopardy-2016-04-20), or 0.1%, at 2,102.40, led by gains in financial and energy stocks, marking a third straight day of gains. The index's close was its highest since Dec. 1. Five reasons why (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/5-reasons-stocks-are-surprisingly-back-near-record-highs-2016-04-20) stocks are surprisingly back near record highs.\nTrump says he would replace Yellen\n\"I would be more inclined to put other people in,\" he told Fortune (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/trump-reverses-course-on-paying-off-debt-says-he-would-replace-yellen-2016-04-20).\nThese are the highest paying companies in the U.S.\nThe financial industry is mostly absent (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/these-are-the-highest-paying-companies-in-the-us-2016-04-20) from the list.\nThe rise and fall of the PC in one chart\nPCs are being left in the dust (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/one-chart-shows-how-mobile-has-crushed-pcs-2016-04-20) by mobile devices such as smartphones and tablets.\nHow UnitedHealth's Obamacare retreat does -- or doesn't -- affect you\nWhat does UnitedHealth Group Inc.'s decision to exit most Obamacare marketplaces next year mean? It depends whom you ask (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/heres-how-does-unitedhealths-obamacare-retreat-does-or-doesnt-affect-you-2016-04-20).\nYour dream of a world without mosquitoes is one step closer to coming true\nThe company behind a proposal to release genetically-engineered mosquitoes (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/your-dream-of-a-world-without-mosquitoes-is-one-step-closer-to-coming-true-2016-04-20) in Florida says their method is more effective than traditional means, such as fumigation.\nWhat to expect from GE earnings\nGeneral Electric Co. is scheduled to release (http://www.marketwatch.com/story/what-to-expect-from-ge-earnings-2016-04-19) first-quarter earnings before the bell on Friday.\n-Priya Anand; 1841ET\n ",
