      "title": "Joel Osteen's Lakewood Church holding job fair for special needs, 'at-risk' young people",
      "text": "Photo: BOB OWEN, Staff Image 1 of / 1 1 Joel Osteen, pastor of Houston's Lakewood Church, was part of an ecumenical group that met June 5, 2014, with Pope Francis at the Vatican. File photo\nJoel Osteen, pastor of Houston's Lakewood Church, was part of an ecumenical group that met June 5, 2014, with Pope Francis at the Vatican. File photo\nPhoto: BOB OWEN, Staff Joel Osteen's Lakewood Church holding job fair for special needs, 'at-risk' young people 1 / 1 Back to Gallery Lakewood Church, the independent mega-church pastored by Joel Osteen, plans Thursday to hold its first-ever job fair specifically for special needs and \"at-risk\" persons ages 16 to 24.\nThe church said in a news release that 60 employers will be at the job fair looking to match work-ready young adults with jobs ranging from internships to full-time positions. Buses will transport more than 300 students from Houston ISD schools, working in partnership with the Department of Rehabilitative Services.\nThe job fair will be held from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. April 28 at the church, 3700 Southwest Freeway in Houston, on the fourth-floor loft. There is no registration fee.\nInformation: Contact 713-212-1661 or jobfair@lakewood.cc, or visit LakewoodChurch.com",
